Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{200%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{100%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn
the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @Butternut Squash{1}(trimmed and halved lengthways), then scoop out
the seeds (peel first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks.

Pop the diced butternut onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer and sprinkle over the
@Black Sesame Seeds{5}. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and cooked through,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}(peeled and thinly
sliced). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and cut the @Lime{1/2}(zested and cut into wedges).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @Thai Green Curry Paste{45%g}. Fry, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Coconut Milk{200%ml} and @Water{50%ml} for
the sauce. Bring to a boil, then turn the heat down to medium and simmer, stirring
occasionally, until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the rice is cooked, fluff up the rice using a #fork{}. Stir through the lime zest
and @Peas{120%g}.

Once the curry sauce has thickened, taste and season with @?salt{}, @?pepper{} and
@?sugar{} if needed. Remove from the heat and add a squeeze of lime juice.

Add half of the roasted black sesame butternut to the curry and stir until coated,
adding a splash of @?water{} if it's a little too thick.

Share the zesty pea rice between your #bowls{}.

Spoon the Thai green style curry over the rice and top with the remaining roasted
black sesame butternut.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!